description: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index seeks to measure the performance of Chinese onshore renminbi ("RMB")-denominated fixed income securities ("RMB Bonds") issued into the China Interbank Bond Market. It is non-diversified.
name: Krane Shares China Credit Index ETF
